1
00:00:01,160 --> 00:00:04,440
Many robotic control
applications,

2
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:06,975
including the lunar
lander application

3
00:00:06,975 --> 00:00:09,060
that you work on in
the practice lab,

4
00:00:09,060 --> 00:00:11,430
have continuous state spaces.

5
00:00:11,430 --> 00:00:12,690
Let's take a look at what that

6
00:00:12,690 --> 00:00:14,399
means and how to generalize

7
00:00:14,399 --> 00:00:16,170
the concept we've
talked about to

8
00:00:16,170 --> 00:00:18,120
these continuous state spaces.

9
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:21,825
A simplify Mars rover
example we use,

10
00:00:21,825 --> 00:00:24,675
I use a discrete set of states,

11
00:00:24,675 --> 00:00:28,290
and what that means is that
simplify Mars rover could

12
00:00:28,290 --> 00:00:32,280
only be in one of six
possible positions.

13
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:35,580
But most robots can be
in more than one of

14
00:00:35,580 --> 00:00:39,405
six or any discrete
number of positions,

15
00:00:39,405 --> 00:00:41,600
instead, they can be in any of

16
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:46,195
a very large number of
continuous value positions.

17
00:00:46,195 --> 00:00:49,025
For example, if the Mars rover

18
00:00:49,025 --> 00:00:52,135
could be anywhere on a line,

19
00:00:52,135 --> 00:00:56,405
so its position was indicated
by a number ranging from

20
00:00:56,405 --> 00:01:01,640
0-6 kilometers where any
number in between is valid.

21
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:06,145
That would be an example of
a continuous state space,

22
00:01:06,145 --> 00:01:08,270
because the position would be

23
00:01:08,270 --> 00:01:11,360
represented by a
number such as that is

24
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:13,835
2.7 kilometers along or

25
00:01:13,835 --> 00:01:17,980
4.8 kilometers or any other
number between zero and six.

26
00:01:17,980 --> 00:01:19,810
Let's look at another example.

27
00:01:19,810 --> 00:01:22,175
I'm going to use
for this example,

28
00:01:22,175 --> 00:01:25,415
the application of
controlling a car or a truck.

29
00:01:25,415 --> 00:01:27,590
Here's a toy car,
Russia toy truck.

30
00:01:27,590 --> 00:01:29,645
This one belongs to my daughter.

31
00:01:29,645 --> 00:01:31,880
If you're building a
self-driving car or

32
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:33,650
self-driving truck and you want

33
00:01:33,650 --> 00:01:35,675
to control this to
drive smoothly,

34
00:01:35,675 --> 00:01:37,865
then the state of this truck

35
00:01:37,865 --> 00:01:40,490
might include a few
numbers such as this,

36
00:01:40,490 --> 00:01:45,485
x position, its y position,
maybe it's orientation.

37
00:01:45,485 --> 00:01:47,065
What way is it facing?

38
00:01:47,065 --> 00:01:49,040
Assuming the truck
stays on the ground,

39
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:50,870
you probably don't need to worry

40
00:01:50,870 --> 00:01:53,225
about how tall is,
how high up it is.

41
00:01:53,225 --> 00:01:56,375
This is state will include x,

42
00:01:56,375 --> 00:01:59,440
y, and is angle Theta,

43
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:02,790
as well as maybe its
speeds in x-direction,

44
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:04,590
the speed in the y-direction,

45
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:06,110
and how quickly it's turning.

46
00:02:06,110 --> 00:02:07,580
Is it turning at one degree

47
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:08,945
per second or is it turning at

48
00:02:08,945 --> 00:02:10,940
30 degrees per second
or is it turning

49
00:02:10,940 --> 00:02:13,615
really quickly at 90
degrees per second?

50
00:02:13,615 --> 00:02:16,740
For a truck or a car,

51
00:02:16,740 --> 00:02:20,885
the state might include
not just one number,

52
00:02:20,885 --> 00:02:23,915
like how many kilometers of
this along on this line,

53
00:02:23,915 --> 00:02:26,180
but they might
includes six numbers,

54
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:27,700
is x position,

55
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:30,800
is y position, is orientation,

56
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:34,505
which I'm going to denote
using Greek alphabet Theta,

57
00:02:34,505 --> 00:02:37,595
as well its velocity
in the x-direction,

58
00:02:37,595 --> 00:02:39,770
which I will denote using x dot,

59
00:02:39,770 --> 00:02:43,765
so that means how quickly is
this x-coordinate changing,

60
00:02:43,765 --> 00:02:46,230
y dot how quickly is the y

61
00:02:46,230 --> 00:02:48,570
coordinate changing,
and then finally,

62
00:02:48,570 --> 00:02:51,050
Theta dot, which
is how quickly is

63
00:02:51,050 --> 00:02:54,745
the angle of the car changing.

64
00:02:54,745 --> 00:02:58,025
Whereas for the 60
Mars rover example,

65
00:02:58,025 --> 00:03:01,620
the state was just one
of six possible numbers.

66
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:03,005
It could be one, two,

67
00:03:03,005 --> 00:03:05,455
three, four, five or six.

68
00:03:05,455 --> 00:03:07,850
For the car, the state would

69
00:03:07,850 --> 00:03:11,530
comprise this vector
of six numbers,

70
00:03:11,530 --> 00:03:13,940
and any of these
numbers can take on

71
00:03:13,940 --> 00:03:17,740
any value within is valid range.

72
00:03:17,740 --> 00:03:20,330
For example, Theta should range

73
00:03:20,330 --> 00:03:23,305
between zero and 360 degrees.

74
00:03:23,305 --> 00:03:25,455
Let's look at another example.

75
00:03:25,455 --> 00:03:26,945
What if you're building

76
00:03:26,945 --> 00:03:28,670
a reinforcement
learning algorithm to

77
00:03:28,670 --> 00:03:31,100
control an autonomous
helicopter,

78
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:34,280
how would you characterize
the position of a helicopter?

79
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,840
To illustrate, I
have with me here

80
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,735
a small toy helicopter.

81
00:03:37,735 --> 00:03:39,830
The positioning of
the helicopter would

82
00:03:39,830 --> 00:03:41,960
include is x position,

83
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:44,360
such as how far north or south

84
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:46,985
is a helicopter, is y position.

85
00:03:46,985 --> 00:03:51,050
Maybe how far on the east-west
axis is the helicopter,

86
00:03:51,050 --> 00:03:52,880
and then also z, the height of

87
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:55,095
the helicopter above ground.

88
00:03:55,095 --> 00:03:57,635
But other than the position,

89
00:03:57,635 --> 00:03:59,030
the helicopter also has

90
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:01,745
an orientation, and
conventionally,

91
00:04:01,745 --> 00:04:03,530
one way to capture
its orientation

92
00:04:03,530 --> 00:04:05,510
is with three
additional numbers,

93
00:04:05,510 --> 00:04:09,170
one of which captures of
the row of the helicopter.

94
00:04:09,170 --> 00:04:11,185
Is it rolling to the
left or the right?

95
00:04:11,185 --> 00:04:12,570
The pitch, is it pitching

96
00:04:12,570 --> 00:04:14,835
forward or pitching
up, pitching back,

97
00:04:14,835 --> 00:04:17,130
and then finally the yaw which

98
00:04:17,130 --> 00:04:19,980
is west the compass
orientation is it facing.

99
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:22,605
If facing north or
east or south or west?

100
00:04:22,605 --> 00:04:25,610
To summarize, the state
of the helicopter

101
00:04:25,610 --> 00:04:30,050
includes is position in the
say, north-south direction,

102
00:04:30,050 --> 00:04:32,545
is positioned in the
east-west direction,

103
00:04:32,545 --> 00:04:34,805
y is height above ground,

104
00:04:34,805 --> 00:04:36,785
and also the row,

105
00:04:36,785 --> 00:04:42,055
the pitch, and also
that yaw of helicopter.

106
00:04:42,055 --> 00:04:43,760
To write this down,

107
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:48,455
the state therefore includes
the position x, y, z,

108
00:04:48,455 --> 00:04:51,845
and then the row pitch,

109
00:04:51,845 --> 00:04:54,500
and yaw denoted with

110
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:59,415
the Greek alphabets
Phi, Theta and Omega.

111
00:04:59,415 --> 00:05:00,860
But to control the helicopter,

112
00:05:00,860 --> 00:05:05,600
we also need to know its
speed in the x-direction,

113
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:08,809
in the y-direction, and
in the z direction,

114
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:11,239
as well as its rate of turning,

115
00:05:11,239 --> 00:05:13,450
also called the
angular velocity.

116
00:05:13,450 --> 00:05:16,970
How fast is this row
changing and how fast is

117
00:05:16,970 --> 00:05:21,485
this pitch changing and how
fast is its yaw changing?

118
00:05:21,485 --> 00:05:23,435
This is actually the state

119
00:05:23,435 --> 00:05:26,030
used to control
autonomous helicopters.

120
00:05:26,030 --> 00:05:31,570
Is this list of 12 numbers
that is input to a policy,

121
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:33,470
and the job of a
policy is look at

122
00:05:33,470 --> 00:05:35,765
these 12 numbers and decide

123
00:05:35,765 --> 00:05:38,530
what's an appropriate action
to take in the helicopter.

124
00:05:38,530 --> 00:05:42,330
So any continuous state
reinforcement learning problem or

125
00:05:42,330 --> 00:05:43,485
a continuous state

126
00:05:43,485 --> 00:05:46,880
Markov decision process,
continuously MTP.

127
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:50,015
The state of the
problem isn't just one

128
00:05:50,015 --> 00:05:52,895
of a small number of
possible discrete values,

129
00:05:52,895 --> 00:05:54,530
like a number from 1-6.

130
00:05:54,530 --> 00:05:58,520
Instead, it's a
vector of numbers,

131
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:03,005
any of which could take any
of a large number of values.

132
00:06:03,005 --> 00:06:05,630
In the practice
lab for this week,

133
00:06:05,630 --> 00:06:06,830
you get to implement for

134
00:06:06,830 --> 00:06:09,125
yourself a reinforcement
learning algorithm

135
00:06:09,125 --> 00:06:13,370
applied to a simulated
lunar lander application.

136
00:06:13,370 --> 00:06:16,685
Landing something on
the moon is simulation.

137
00:06:16,685 --> 00:06:18,815
Let's take a look in
the next video at

138
00:06:18,815 --> 00:06:20,960
what that application entails,

139
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:25,110
since there will be another
